## 📐 Typography Hierarchy

### Font Families
```css
--font-display:     'Druk Wide Bold'     /* Titles, labels, strong UI */
--font-serif-hero:  'Moret'              /* Editorial numbers, scores */
--font-ui:          'Inter'              /* Eyebrows, small labels */
--font-sans:        'Inter'              /* Body text */
```

### Type Scales

#### Display (Main Titles)
```css
--text-display-xl: 96px   /* Hero headlines */
--text-display-lg: 64px   /* Section titles */
--text-display-md: 48px   /* Card titles */
--text-display-sm: 32px   /* Subtitles */
```

#### Editorial (Numbers/Scores)
```css
--text-editorial-xl: 84px   /* Giant scores */
--text-editorial-lg: 48px   /* Highlight numbers */
--text-editorial-md: 32px   /* Stats */
--text-editorial-sm: 24px   /* Metrics */
```

#### UI (Interface)
```css
--text-ui-lg: 16px   /* Large buttons */
--text-ui-md: 14px   /* Standard buttons */
--text-ui-sm: 12px   /* Labels */
--text-ui-xs: 11px   /* Eyebrows, tags */
```

### Usage Patterns

#### Eyebrow (Supertitle)
```tsx
<div className="ole-eyebrow !text-neon-yellow" style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-ui)' }}>
  <span>Next match · {fixture.kickoffLabel}</span>
</div>
```
- Font: `--font-ui` (Inter)
- Size: `10px` or `11px`
- Weight: `600` (semibold)
- Tracking: `0.22em` (very spaced)
- Transform: `uppercase`
- Color: `--yellow` or `text-black/70` (on yellow)

#### Editorial Headline (Moret Italic)
```tsx
<p className="italic text-neon-yellow leading-none tabular-nums"
   style={{
     fontFamily: 'var(--font-serif-hero)',
     fontWeight: 700,
     fontSize: 'clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.75rem)',
     letterSpacing: '-0.03em',
   }}>
  {supportLabel}%
</p>
```
- Font: `--font-serif-hero` (Moret)
- Style: `italic`
- Weight: `700`
- Tracking: `-0.03em` (tight)
- Use: Large numbers, scores, highlight values

#### Display Headline (Druk)
```tsx
<h3 className="text-xl font-display font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-white">
  Friendly
</h3>
```
- Font: `--font-display` (Druk Wide Bold)
- Weight: `900` (black)
- Transform: `uppercase`
- Tracking: `0.2em` (wide)
- Use: Section titles, CTAs, strong labels

